    "summary": "Passionate particle physicist.\nUsed to be based at CERN, now I am in Amsterdam.\n\nPart of the ATLAS collaboration with the ITk group of Nikhef (The Netherlands), assembling the endcaps of the ATLAS inner tracker detector of the Large Hadron Collider LHC. \n\nPart of the Postdoc Committee of Nikhef.\n\nWorked on the characterization of high radiation tolerant pixelated silicon sensors for the CMS Inner Tracker with the IFCA (Spain) Instrumentation group.\n\nActive in outreach, bringing science to everybody and supporting the women role in science.\nProficient in Spanish and English, fluent in French, and currently learning Dutch.\nInterested in bouldering and yoga among other sports, traveling, dancing bachata, painting, diplomacy, and much more!",
